President Muhammadu Buhari hosted the 2022 committee of business, political, media and civil society leaders to a dinner in Abuja on Sunday. Nduka Obaigbena, convener of the committee, said the aim of the committee is to defend Nigeria in a time of crisis and in a time of transition. Kayode Fayemi, Ekiti state governor; Dave Umahi, Ebonyi state governor, and other leaders attended the dinner. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-657181" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/20220201_113521-1024x580.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="510" /> <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-657182" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/20220201_113525-1024x641.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="563" /> <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-657183" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/20220201_113529-1024x576.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="506" /> <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-657184" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/20220201_113532-1024x671.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="590" />